{"title_page": "Still Rolling Stones", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name          = Still Rolling Stones\n| cover         =Still Rolling Stones.jpg\n| alt           = \n| border        = yes\n| type          = single\n| artist        = [[Lauren Daigle]]\n| album         = [[Look Up Child]]\n| released      = {{start date|2020|4|10}}\n| format        =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded      = 2017\u201318\n| studio        = \n| genre         = \n*[[Contemporary R&B|R&B/Soul]]\n*[[contemporary Christian music]]\n| length        = 4:08\n| label         = [[Centricity Music|Centricity]]\n| writer        = \n*[[Jason Ingram]]\n*Paul Mabury\n*Paul Duncan\n*Lauren Daigle\n| producer      = \n* Jason Ingram\n* Paul Mabury\n|misc=\n| prev_title = [[Rescue (Lauren Daigle song)|Rescue]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n}}\n\n\"'''Still Rolling Stones\"''' is a song performed by American [[contemporary Christian music]] singer and songwriter [[Lauren Daigle]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.patheos.com/blogs/reelfaith/2018/07/listen-new-lauren-daigle-song-you-say-new-album-coming-soon.html|title=LISTEN: New Lauren Daigle Song 'You Say,' New Album Coming Soon |publisher=Patheos|accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/look-up-child/1409149359|title=Look Up Child by Lauren Daigle |publisher=iTunes|accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref> The song was written  by Daigle, Paul Mabury, Jason Ingram, and Paul Duncan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.praisecharts.com/songs/details/71603/still-rolling-stones-sheet-music|work=PraiseCharts|title=Still Rolling Stones - Lauren Daigle (Look Up Child) }}</ref> \n\nIt peaked at No. 11 on the US [[Hot Christian Songs]] chart.\n\n==Background==\nDaigle initially released \"Still Rolling Stones\" as the first promotional single on August 10, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://jesuswired.com/2018/08/13/lauren-daigle-releases-new-song-still-rolling-stones/|title = Lauren Daigle Releases New Song Still Rolling Stones|access-date = November 22, 2018|date = August 13, 2018|publisher = JesusWired}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = https://centricitymusic.com/lauren-daigle-reveals-additional-details-on-forthcoming-album-look-up-child/|title = Lauren Daigle Reveals Additional Details on Forthcoming Album \"Look Up Child\"|access-date = November 22, 2018|date = August 10, 2018|publisher = CentricityMusic}}</ref> It is also the first track on the album.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://genius.com/albums/Lauren-daigle/Look-up-child|title = Look Up Child Tracklist|access-date = November 22, 2018|date = September 7, 2018 |publisher = Genius}}</ref> Lauren describes the track,\"\"Still Rolling Stones\" will be the first track on the new album, because it makes a statement. \"Out of the shadows...\" will be the first line you hear when you start to play ''Look Up Child''. It's all about the things we think are dead, and a reminder that all losses can be revived. They can all come back. The track is at times wild, vibrant, and loud. Then it sounds rich & soulful - giving you a glimpse into what is to be expected on the album.\"<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.lifefm.co.nz/music/item/4478-lauren-daigle-still-rolling-stones|title = Lauren Daigle: Still Rolling Stones|access-date = November 22, 2018|date = August 13, 2018|publisher = JesusWired}}</ref>\n\n\"Still Rolling Stones\" will impact Christian radio on April 10, 2020, as the fourth single from ''Look Up Child''.<ref name=\"Daily Play MPE\">{{cite web |url= https://daily.plaympe.com/lauren-daigle-still-rolling-stones-album/ |title= Lauren Daigle - Still Rolling Stones (Album) - Daily Play MPE\u00aeDaily Play MPE\u00ae |date= March 13, 2020 |website= Daily Play MPE\u00ae |publisher= Destiny Media Technologies Inc. |access-date= March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"Still Rolling Stones\" is originally in the key of E minor, with a tempo of 99 [[beats per minute]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Still Rolling Stones By Lauren Daigle |url=https://tunebat.com/Info/Still-Rolling-Stones-Lauren-Daigle/2aeXjKQmYBckzx6WvOZiuj |website=TuneBat |accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref> Written in [[common time]], Daigle's vocal range spans from [[D (musical note)|D<sub>4</sub>]] to [[C (musical note)|C<sub>5</sub>]] during the song.<ref>{{cite web |title=Still Rolling Stones By Lauren Daigle |url=https://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0188308#ProductDetails |website=www.musicnotes.com |accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\nIt debuted at No. 17 on the ''Billboard'' Christian Songs chart on the issue week of August 25, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/christian-songs/2018-08-25|title=Music: Christian Music Chart - Billboard Chart |work=billboard.com |accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref> After the release of ''Look Up Child'', it jumped to No. 16.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/christian-songs/2018-09-22|title=Music: Top 100 Songs - Billboard Hot 100 Chart |work=billboard.com |accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref> After being premiered on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'', it reached its peak of No. 11 on its twelfth week on the chart.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/christian-songs/2018-11-10|title=Music: Christian Music Chart - Billboard Chart |work=billboard.com |accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\"tidal\">{{cite web|title=Look Up Child / Lauren Daigle|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/101244256|publisher=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|date=August 21, 2019|accessdate=August 21, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Lauren Daigle]]&nbsp;\u2013 vocals, songwriter\n*[[Jason Ingram]] \u2013 songwriter\n*Paul Duncan \u2013 songwriter\n*Joe La Porta \u2013 mastering engineer\n\n== Live performances ==\nDaigle performed the song on television for the first time on ''The Ellen DeGeneres Show''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gatewaynews.co.za/lauren-daigle-performs-hit-song-on-the-ellen-show/|title=Lauren Daigle performs hit song on \u2018The Ellen Show\u2019|date=October 25, 2018|publisher=}}</ref> She also performed the track on ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' on October 7, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/country/8532432/lauren-daigle-performs-still-rolling-stones-late-night|title=Lauren Daigle Inspires With Soulful 'Still Rolling Stones' Performance On 'Late Night'|date=October 11, 2019|publisher=Billboard}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018\u201320)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br/>position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| UK [[Cross Rhythms|'' Cross Rhythms'' Weekly Chart]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crossrhythms.co.uk/chart/?date=20181028|title=UK Cross Rhythms Weekly Chart|work=Cross Rhythms|date=October 28, 2018|accessdate=June 9, 2019}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardchristiansongs|11|artist=Lauren Daigle|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 26, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardchristianairplay|33|artist=Lauren Daigle|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 14, 2020}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| UK ''Cross Rhythms'' Annual Chart<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.crossrhythms.co.uk/chart/?year=2018|title = Cross Rhythms\u2013 Year-End 2018 |work = Cross Rhythms |access-date = July 8, 2019}}</ref>\n| 3\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US Christian Songs (''Billboard'')<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2018/hot-christian-songs|title = Hot Christian Songs \u2013 Year-End 2018 |work = Billboard|access-date = 4 December 2018}}</ref>\n| 47\n|-\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US Christian Songs (''Billboard'')<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2019/hot-christian-songs|title = Hot Christian Songs \u2013 Year-End 2019 |work = Billboard|access-date = December 5, 2019}}</ref>\n| 79\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| United States\n| April 10, 2020\n| [[Christian radio]]\n| [[Centricity Music|Centricity]]\n| <ref name=\"Daily Play MPE\" />\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Lauren Daigle}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|lauren-daigle|still-rolling-stones}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n[[Category:2018 singles]]\n[[Category:2018 songs]]\n[[Category:Lauren Daigle songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Jason Ingram]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name          = Still Rolling Stones\n| cover         =Still Rolling Stones.jpg\n| alt           = \n| border        = yes\n| type          = single\n| artist        = [[Lauren Daigle]]\n| album         = [[Look Up Child]]\n| released      = {{start date|2020|4|10}}\n| format        =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded      = 2017\u201318\n| studio        = \n| genre         = \n*[[Contemporary R&B|R&B/Soul]]\n*[[contemporary Christian music]]\n| length        = 4:08\n| label         = [[Centricity Music|Centricity]]\n| writer        = \n*[[Jason Ingram]]\n*Paul Mabury\n*Paul Duncan\n*Lauren Daigle\n| producer      = \n* Jason Ingram\n* Paul Mabury\n|misc=\n| prev_title = [[Rescue (Lauren Daigle song)|Rescue]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n}}\n\n\"'''Still Rolling Stones\"''' is a song performed by American [[contemporary Christian music]] singer and songwriter [[Lauren Daigle]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.patheos.com/blogs/reelfaith/2018/07/listen-new-lauren-daigle-song-you-say-new-album-coming-soon.html|title=LISTEN: New Lauren Daigle Song 'You Say,' New Album Coming Soon |publisher=Patheos|accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/look-up-child/1409149359|title=Look Up Child by Lauren Daigle |publisher=iTunes|accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref> The song was written  by Daigle, Paul Mabury, Jason Ingram, and Paul Duncan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.praisecharts.com/songs/details/71603/still-rolling-stones-sheet-music|work=PraiseCharts|title=Still Rolling Stones - Lauren Daigle (Look Up Child) }}</ref> \n\nIt peaked at No. 11 on the US [[Hot Christian Songs]] chart.\n\n==Background==\nDaigle initially released \"Still Rolling Stones\" as the first promotional single on August 10, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://jesuswired.com/2018/08/13/lauren-daigle-releases-new-song-still-rolling-stones/|title = Lauren Daigle Releases New Song Still Rolling Stones|access-date = November 22, 2018|date = August 13, 2018|publisher = JesusWired}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = https://centricitymusic.com/lauren-daigle-reveals-additional-details-on-forthcoming-album-look-up-child/|title = Lauren Daigle Reveals Additional Details on Forthcoming Album \"Look Up Child\"|access-date = November 22, 2018|date = August 10, 2018|publisher = CentricityMusic}}</ref> It is also the first track on the album.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://genius.com/albums/Lauren-daigle/Look-up-child|title = Look Up Child Tracklist|access-date = November 22, 2018|date = September 7, 2018 |publisher = Genius}}</ref> Lauren describes the track,\"\"Still Rolling Stones\" will be the first track on the new album, because it makes a statement. \"Out of the shadows...\" will be the first line you hear when you start to play ''Look Up Child''. It's all about the things we think are dead, and a reminder that all losses can be revived. They can all come back. The track is at times wild, vibrant, and loud. Then it sounds rich & soulful - giving you a glimpse into what is to be expected on the album.\"<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.lifefm.co.nz/music/item/4478-lauren-daigle-still-rolling-stones|title = Lauren Daigle: Still Rolling Stones|access-date = November 22, 2018|date = August 13, 2018|publisher = JesusWired}}</ref>\n\n\"Still Rolling Stones\" will impact Christian radio on April 10, 2020, as the fourth single from ''Look Up Child''.<ref name=\"Daily Play MPE\">{{cite web |url= https://daily.plaympe.com/lauren-daigle-still-rolling-stones-album/ |title= Lauren Daigle - Still Rolling Stones (Album) - Daily Play MPE\u00aeDaily Play MPE\u00ae |date= March 13, 2020 |website= Daily Play MPE\u00ae |publisher= Destiny Media Technologies Inc. |access-date= March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"Still Rolling Stones\" is originally in the key of E minor, with a tempo of 99 [[beats per minute]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Still Rolling Stones By Lauren Daigle |url=https://tunebat.com/Info/Still-Rolling-Stones-Lauren-Daigle/2aeXjKQmYBckzx6WvOZiuj |website=TuneBat |accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref> Written in [[common time]], Daigle's vocal range spans from [[D (musical note)|D<sub>4</sub>]] to [[C (musical note)|C<sub>5</sub>]] during the song.<ref>{{cite web |title=Still Rolling Stones By Lauren Daigle |url=https://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0188308#ProductDetails |website=www.musicnotes.com |accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\nIt debuted at No. 17 on the ''Billboard'' Christian Songs chart on the issue week of August 25, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/christian-songs/2018-08-25|title=Music: Christian Music Chart - Billboard Chart |work=billboard.com |accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref> After the release of ''Look Up Child'', it jumped to No. 16.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/christian-songs/2018-09-22|title=Music: Top 100 Songs - Billboard Hot 100 Chart |work=billboard.com |accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref> After being premiered on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'', it reached its peak of No. 11 on its twelfth week on the chart.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/christian-songs/2018-11-10|title=Music: Christian Music Chart - Billboard Chart |work=billboard.com |accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\"tidal\">{{cite web|title=Look Up Child / Lauren Daigle|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/101244256|publisher=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|date=August 21, 2019|accessdate=August 21, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Lauren Daigle]]&nbsp;\u2013 vocals, songwriter\n*[[Jason Ingram]] \u2013 songwriter\n*Paul Duncan \u2013 songwriter\n*Joe La Porta \u2013 mastering engineer\n\n== Live performances ==\nDaigle performed the song on television for the first time on ''The Ellen DeGeneres Show''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gatewaynews.co.za/lauren-daigle-performs-hit-song-on-the-ellen-show/|title=Lauren Daigle performs hit song on \u2018The Ellen Show\u2019|date=October 25, 2018|publisher=}}</ref> She also performed the track on ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' on October 7, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/country/8532432/lauren-daigle-performs-still-rolling-stones-late-night|title=Lauren Daigle Inspires With Soulful 'Still Rolling Stones' Performance On 'Late Night'|date=October 11, 2019|publisher=Billboard}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018\u201320)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br/>position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| UK [[Cross Rhythms|'' Cross Rhythms'' Weekly Chart]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www