}</ref>\n*[[4 December]] - [[Louise of Great Britain|Princess Louise of Wales]], daughter of the Prince and Princess of Wales (died [[1751 in Wales|1751]])\n*''date unknown'' - [[George Rice (died 1779)|George Rice]], politician (died [[1779 in Wales|1779]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1754-1790/member/rice-george-1724-79|title=RICE, George (?1724-79), of Newton Castle, Carm.|website=History of Parliament Online|accessdate = 25 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Deaths==\n*[[8 January]] - [[Mary Herbert, Marchioness of Powis]], age unknown<ref>{{cite ODNB|id=13061|title=Herbert, William|first=Paul|last=Hopkins}}</ref>\n*[[22 March]] - [[John Evans (bishop)|John Evans]], Bishop of Bangor and Meath, 73?<ref>{{cite DNB|wstitle=Evans, John (d.1724)}}</ref>\n*[[1 June]] - [[Erasmus Saunders]], clergyman, 54?\n*[[4 June]] - [[Richard Bulkeley, 4th Viscount Bulkeley]], 41<ref>{{cite web|last1=Thomas|first1=Peter D.G.|title=Bulkeley, Richard, 4th Visct. Bulkeley [I] (1682-1724), of Baron Hill, Anglesey|url=http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1715-1754/member/bulkeley-richard-1682-1724|website=[[The History of Parliament]]|accessdate=25 August 2014}}</ref>\n*[[15 December]] - [[Stephen Parry (Welsh MP)|Stephen Parry]], MP for Cardigan Boroughs, 49<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1715-1754/member/parry-stephen-1675-1724| title=PARRY, Stephen (1675-1724), of Neuadd Trefawr, Card. | publisher= History of Parliament Online| accessdate = 18 August 2018}}</ref>\n*''date unknown'' - [[Jeremiah Jones (tutor)|Jeremiah Jones]], independent tutor and biblical critic, 30/31<ref>{{DNB|wstitle=Jones, Jeremiah|volume=30}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Year in Europe|1724}}\n\n[[Category:Years of the 18th century in Wales]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Welsh English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Year in Wales header|1724}}\nThis article is about the particular significance of the year '''1724''' to [[Wales]] and [[Welsh people|its people]].\n\n==Incumbents==\n*[[Prince of Wales]] - [[George II of Great Britain|George]] (later George II)\n*[[Princess of Wales]] - [[Caroline of Ansbach]]\n\n==Events==\n*The [[Shire Hall, Monmouth]], is built.<ref>{{cite book|author=Alfred John Taylor|title=Monmouth Castle and Great Castle House, Monmouthshire|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CksjAAAAMAAJ|year=1951|publisher=H.M. Stationery Office|page=20}}</ref>\n*A [[charity school]] is built at [[Caerleon]] as the result of a bequest from Charles Williams.<ref>{{cite book|title=Cylchgrawn Hanes Cymru|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RYpnAAAAMAAJ|year=1980|publisher=University of Wales Press|page=276}}</ref>\n*The title of [[Baron Bergavenny]] is inherited by [[William Nevill, 16th Baron Bergavenny|William Nevill]].\n\n==Arts and literature==\n\n===New books===\n*[[William Wynne (lawyer)|William Wynne]] - ''The Life of Sir [[Leoline Jenkins]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://biography.wales/article/s-WYNN-OWE-1652|title=WYNNE, OWEN (1652-?), civil servant|website=Welsh Biography Online|publisher=[[National Library of Wales]]|author=[[A. H. Dodd]]|access-date=25 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Births==\n*April - Joshua Eddowes, printer and bookseller (died [[1811 in Wales|1811]])\n*[[17 May]] - [[Gabriel Jones (Virginia)|Gabriel Jones]], Welsh American lawyer, legislator, court clerk and civil servant (died 1806) \n*[[22 September]] - [[John Parry (1724\u20131797)|John Parry]], lawyer and politician (died [[1797 in Wales|1797]])<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1754-1790/member/parry-john-1724-97|title = PARRY, John (1724\u201397), of Wernfawr, Caern.|publisher= History of Parliament Online|accessdate = 25 June 2018}}</ref>\n*[[4 December]] - [[Louise of Great Britain|Princess Louise of Wales]], daughter of the Prince and Princess of Wales (died [[1751 in Wales|1751]])\n*''date unknown'' - [[George Rice (died 1779)|George Rice]], politician (died [[1779 in Wales|1779]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1754-1790/member/rice-george-1724-79|title=RICE, George (?1724-79), of Newton Castle, Carm.|website=History of Parliament Online|accessdate = 25 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Deaths==\n*[[8 January]] - [[Mary Herbert, Marchioness of Powis]], age unknown<ref>{{cite ODNB|id=13061|title=Herbert, William|first=Paul|last=Hopkins}}</ref>\n*[[22 March]] - [[John Evans (bishop)|John Evans]], Bishop of Bangor and Meath, 73?<ref>{{cite DNB|wstitle=Evans, John (d.1724)}}</ref>\n*[[1 June]] - [[Erasmus Saunders]], clergyman, 54?\n*[[4 June]] - [[Richard Bulkeley, 4th Viscount Bulkeley]], 41<ref>{{cite web|last1=Thomas|first1=Peter D.G.|title=Bulkeley, Richard, 4th Visct. Bulkeley [I] (1682-1724), of Baron Hill, Anglesey|url=http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1715-1754/member/bulkeley-richard-1682-1724|website=[[The History of Parliament]]|accessdate=25 August 2014}}</ref>\n*[[15 December]] - [[Stephen Parry (Welsh MP)|Stephen Parry]], MP for Cardigan Boroughs, 49<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1715-1754/member/parry-stephen-1675-1724| title=PARRY, Stephen (1675-1724), of Neuadd Trefawr, Card. | publisher= History of Parliament Online| accessdate = 18 August 2018}}</ref>\n*''date unknown'' - [[Jeremiah Jones (tutor)|Jeremiah Jones]], independent tutor and biblical critic, 30/31<ref>{{DNB|wstitle=Jones, Jeremiah|volume=30}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Year in Europe|1724}}\n\n{{uncategorized|date=April 2020}}\n", "name_user": "Deb", "label": "safe", "comment": "cat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1724_in_Wales"}
